# Benchmark conventions

**Strict builds:** [strict-by-default](../../docs/ecosystem/strict-by-default.md) · `.cursor/rules/li-strict-by-default.mdc` — benchmark Li must **`lic build --release`**; `extern proc` always has `requires`/`ensures`; no bench-only proof bypass.

**Package ↔ bench mapping:** [package-suite-coverage-audit](../../docs/benchmarks/package-suite-coverage-audit.md) · agents: `.cursor/rules/li-package-benchmark-suites.mdc`.

Plan: `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-14-benchmarks-and-simulations.md`

## Before timing

1. Shared `params.toml` across li and reference impls (C++, Rust, Julia, Python)
2. `verify.py` must pass (energy drift, momentum, trajectory hash)
3. **`lic build` must succeed** on all benchmark Li sources (Lean verify when enabled for that target) — **not** `lic check` alone
4. Document flags: `lic build --release`, Clang `-O3 -march=native`

## Tiers

| Tier | Examples |
|------|----------|
| 0 | compile-time shape traps |
| 2 | `three_body`, `md_lennard_jones`, PDE stencils |
| 3 | `mlp_forward`, MNIST subset |

## Reporting

- CSV columns: `benchmark, lang, threads, metric, value, unit, cpu_model, flags`
- Label BLAS/NumPy/PyTorch columns explicitly — never compare naive Python to SIMD li without labeling
- Regression: investigate if li > 1.2× C++ on Tier 1–2 on the same machine
- **Social:** run `./scripts/plot_shareables.sh` before posting benchmark or CI results to X

Plot spec: `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-14-plots-and-social.md`

## Reference impls

Each Tier 2+ benchmark needs a C++ reference that passes `verify.py` before li numbers are published.

## tier5_http (li-httpd / `lis`)

Config lives in **TOML only** (`benchmarks/tier5_http/`). Do not hardcode scenarios in Python.

- Merge: `defaults.toml` ← `scenarios/*/bench.toml`
- Harness: `verify_http.py`, `bench_http.py`, `exploit_http.py`, `audit_nginx_src.py`
- CI: `lis/scripts/verify-http.sh`
